/android/app/debug
/android/app/profile
/android/app/release

# Project docs policy — only README + the dev progress log are versioned.
# Everything else (PROJECT.md spec, PLAN.md phases, rules.md, etc.) is
# AI-working / planning material kept locally.
*.md
!README.md
!documentation.md

# ─── Sensitive ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Firebase config — generated per-developer via `flutterfire configure`.
# Firebase API keys aren't true secrets (Firebase security comes from
# Firestore Rules + Auth, not key secrecy — see
# https://firebase.google.com/docs/projects/api-keys), but we keep them
# untracked so each developer points the app at their own Firebase project
# during development and to silence repo secret-scanners.
lib/firebase_options.dart
firebase.json
firestore.rules
firestore.indexes.json
android/app/google-services.json
ios/Runner/GoogleService-Info.plist
macos/Runner/GoogleService-Info.plist
ios/firebase_app_id_file.json
macos/firebase_app_id_file.json

# Generic secret patterns
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key
secrets/
**/credentials.json

# Claude / AI tooling local state
.claude/
.aider*
